Compu-Clearing Outsourcing, Lonmin May Move: South African Stock Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-04-12T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/compu-clearing-outsourcing-lonmin-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined 574.56, or 1.8
percent, to 32,239.87 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Compu-Clearing Outsourcing Ltd. (CCL)  : The freight
forwarding and clearing company said it has withdrawn from
unspecified talks with an unnamed party. The negotiations were
initially announced on December 2. The stock was unchanged at
2.99 rand.  Lonmin Plc (LON)  : The world’s third-largest platinum
producer shut a shaft at its Marikana operation in South Africa
following the company’s sixth fatal accident so far this fiscal
year. Lonmin will halt all mining for a safety audit on April
14. The stock declined 5.80 rand, or 3 percent, to 185.45 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  